                     /note="Phage phi80 bacterial attachment site attB, within
                     the 3′ end of gene yciI (b1251), divergent from and
                     adjacent to tonB — reconciling the historical 'tonB region
                     / ~28 min' lore (beside tonB, not in it; not a tRNA gene).
                     54 bp window from NC_000913.3 containing the 15 bp core
                     consensus AACACTTTCTTAAAT; the exact 17 bp common core and
                     crossover (Leong et al. 1985) are behind paywalls and the
                     precise boundaries are PROVISIONAL. Cognate phage site:
                     phi80_attP."
